<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, on line 915 of Zend_Form_Element, a call to ReflectionClass::newInstanceArgs() can fail with a catchable fatal error if the options passed to addValidator() are not in an array.</p>

<p>This can be rectified in one of two ways:
* typehint $options as an array
* case $options to an array at the time that the call is made</p>

<p>This is true also of addFilter().</p>

